comments: Harris (DEN) reaches in and makes marginal contact with Holiday's (NOP) arm. Holiday maintains control of the ball and continues his drive.
Holiday (NOP) lifts his pivot foot and releases the ball to dribble prior to returning his foot to the floor.
Craig (DEN) makes contact to the Favors' (NOP) arm during his upward shooting motion and the contact affects his shot attempt near the rim.
During the driving shot attempt, Favors' (NOP) arm makes incidental contact with Jokic's (DEN) head while he simultaneously makes contact with the ball.
Grant (DEN) veers into Hart's (NOP) path in transition and initiates contact that affects Hart's SQBR.
Favors (NOP) makes contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it from Craig (DEN) during the rebound.
Jokic (DEN) slightly turns and initiates marginal contact to Hart (NOP) during the pick.
Ingram (NOP) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Favors (NOP) briefly places a hand on Jokic's (DEN) body during the pick but he immediately removes his hand. The contact is marginal and Jokic's reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Ingram (NOP) makes marginal contact to Barton's (DEN) body that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
During the inbound, Harris (DEN) and Redick (NOP) briefly engage in marginal contact prior to separating as both players move around the screen.
Favors (NOP) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Harris' (DEN) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the screen.
Craig (DEN) turns and continues to maintain a legal guarding position along Holiday's (NOP) path during his driving shot attempt.
Craig (DEN) absorbs the oncoming body contact from Ingram (NOP) during his driving shot attempt. The contact is marginal.
